# Deployment and environments

## Local development

- Requirements: Node 24.14+, PNPM 10+, MySQL 8, Redis (see README.md)
- Quick start:
  - cp .env.example .env
  - docker compose up -d (provisions MySQL at 127.0.0.1:3309 and Redis at 127.0.0.1:6380)
  - pnpm --filter dineros-app exec prisma migrate deploy
  - pnpm dev (Nuxt at http://localhost:3000)

Notes for cloud dev environments (AGENTS.md): override any injected production DATABASE_URL with your local value before running prisma or dev server.

## Docker images

- app/Dockerfile: multi-stage; runs prisma generate with placeholder DATABASE_URL, builds Nuxt, copies .output and prisma into a slim runner
- microservice/Dockerfile: multi-stage; prisma generate; main runner uses pnpm runtime; additional target runner-keyrotate includes kubectl+jq for staging key rotation CronJob

## CI/CD (GitHub Actions)

- PR checks (.github/workflows/pr.yml)
  - Jobs: lint, test (Vitest), pre-commit security (TruffleHog + hooks), CodeQL
  - If PR branch is in repo, build images for main app and microservice and deploy to staging GKE namespace via .deploy/dineros.template.yaml
  - Optional: post a "bugbot run" comment for Cursor Bugbot (if PAT provided)
- Main branch deploy (.github/workflows/main.yml)
  - Build app and microservice images, push to gcr.io (Workload Identity)
  - Deploy production using the same templated manifest and verify rollout (health/ready)
- Sonar (manual) (.github/workflows/sonar.yml): runs coverage and Sonar scan
- CodeQL weekly schedule (.github/workflows/codeql.yml)

## Kubernetes manifests (templated)

- .deploy/dineros.template.yaml: renders both main app and microservice Deployments + Services + Ingress with envsubst
  - Uses secrets references for DB (SECRET_DB), DATABASE_URL (SECRET_DATABASE_MAIN/SECRET_DATABASE_MICRO), app secrets (SECRET_APP), JWT (SECRET_JWT), Google SA secret (SECRET_GA)
  - MICROSERVICE_INTERNAL_URL used by main app to reach the microservice in-cluster
  - Health probes: /health/live and /health/ready
- Staging key rotation
  - .deploy/key-rotation-cronjob.template.yaml — nightly job using microservice :keyrotate image to patch K8S secret and orchestrate restarts, then call microservice /migrate
  - .deploy/key-rotation-rbac.template.yaml — Role/RoleBinding permitting secrets and deployments patch. Applying requires GKE IAM permissions (see AGENTS.md and action description)

## Environment variables (representative)

- Database: DATABASE_URL (in per-app secret), field encryption bundle in SECRET_DB (DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY, DB_DECRYPTION_KEY_*)
- Redis: REDIS_HOST, REDIS_PORT
- External: PLAID_CLIENT_ID/SECRET, POSTMARK_SERVER_TOKEN/WEBHOOK_SECRET, OPENAI_API_KEY, TWILIO_*
- Auth/security: JWT_SECRET, RSA keys managed via Rsa model in DB (rotation handled at app level)
- Runtime: DEPLOY_ENV, NUXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL, MICROSERVICE_INTERNAL_URL

See .env.example for a comprehensive list and app/server/envSchema.ts for validation.
